FBIS3-31625 "dreeu035_p_94015" FBIS-EEU-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 POLAND Longest Postwar Miners Strike Ends LD1902174894 Warsaw TV Polonia Network in Polish 1600 GMT 19 Feb 94 LD1902174894 Warsaw TV Polonia Network Language: Polish Article Type:BFN [Text] The longest strike in the post-war history of Poland ended last night. After 19 days, 78 miners from the Pomorzany mine [belonging to the Boleslaw Mining and Metallurgical Plant] returned to the surface. A signed agreement guarantees the miners a pay rise of 1.5 million zlotys a month and a quarterly bonus based on the enterprise's profits. According to the director of the Boleslaw mining and metallurgical plant this is all the enterprise can manage at the moment.
